@startuml
title IP Spoofing - Conceptual Flow

actor Attacker
participant "Target Server" as Server
participant "Trusted Host" as Trusted

Attacker ->> Server: Send packet\nsource IP = Trusted Host
Server ->> Trusted: Send response to spoofed address

note over Trusted
Trusted host receives an
unexpected response because
it never sent the request
end note

note over Server
Server believes the packet
originated from the trusted host
because the source IP was forged
end note

note over Attacker
Used for hiding origin,
bypassing simple IP-based trust,
or enabling reflection attacks
end note

@enduml